BUCHWALD--Art. The American Academy of Arts and Letters notes with sorrows the death of our esteemed colleague. His loss will be deeply felt.
$(6$)BUCHWALD--Art. The National Center on Addiction and Substance Abuse (CASA) at Columbia University mourns the loss of Art Buchwald, a very special supporter, who was invaluable to us from the very beggining. I mourn the loss of a very dear friend with whom I shared many meals, Redskin football games, and laughter, and who lit up many Easters for my children Mark, Joe, and Claudia, and special birthdays for my wife Hilary and me. We all love him and our hearts and prayers go to his family. Joseph A Califano, Jr.
$(6$)BUCHWALD--Art. The Officers, Governors and Members of the Friars Club deeply mourn the loss of their beloved friend and esteemed member, Friar Art Buchwald. We are honored and proud to have been touched by this artistic genius, and we extend our sincere condolences to his family. Jerry Lewis, Abbot Freddie Roman, Dean Stewie Stone, Prior Fred C. Klein, Treasurer Stu Cantor, Scribe Jean-Pierre Trebot, Executive Director
